Below is a simple HTML file for a "Crack Drug Dealer Simulator" game. This is a basic version showcasing simple mechanics like buying and selling drugs, keeping track of your money, and managing your inventory. You can copy this code into a single HTML file and open it in a web browser to run the game.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Crack Drug Dealer Simulator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #2c3e50;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        #game {
            border: 1px solid #ecf0f1;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #34495e;
            border-radius: 5px;
            display: inline-block;
        }
        button {
            background-color: #e74c3c;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            margin: 5px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #c0392b;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="game">
        <h1>Crack Drug Dealer Simulator</h1>
        <p id="money">Money: $100</p>
        <p id="inventory">Inventory: 0 grams</p>
        <button onclick="buyDrugs()">Buy 1g ($50)</button>
        <button onclick="sellDrugs()">Sell 1g ($75)</button>
        <p id="message"></p>
    </div>

    <script>
        let money = 100;
        let inventory = 0;

        function buyDrugs() {
            if (money >= 50) {
                money -= 50;
                inventory++;
                updateDisplay();
                setMessage("You bought 1 gram of crack.");
            } else {
                setMessage("Not enough money to buy drugs.");
            }
        }

        function sellDrugs() {
            if (inventory > 0) {
                money += 75;
                inventory--;
                updateDisplay();
                setMessage("You sold 1 gram of crack.");
            } else {
                setMessage("You have no drugs to sell.");
            }
        }

        function updateDisplay() {
            document.getElementById("money").innerText = "Money: $" + money;
            document.getElementById("inventory").innerText = "Inventory: " + inventory + " grams";
        }

        function setMessage(msg) {
            document.getElementById("message").innerText = msg;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the code above.
2. Open a text editor (like Notepad, VSCode, etc.) and paste the code into it.
3. Save the file with a `.html` extension, like `drug_dealer_simulator.html`.
4. Open the saved HTML file in a web browser.

### Game Mechanics:
- You start with $100 and no inventory.
- You can buy drugs for $50 each, increasing your inventory by 1 gram.
- You can sell drugs for $75 each, decreasing your inventory by 1 gram.
- The game displays messages for transactions and updates money and inventory counts. 

### Note:
This game is a simple simulation for educational purposes only. It deals with sensitive subjects and does not promote illegal activities. Always use discretion and consider the implications of the game's theme in real life.
